race.comment: TRULY GALLANT (1) bolted in on debut before a 0.6L defeat most recently over the 1420m journey here most recently. He looks a nice horse on the rise and now out to the mile trip which looks to suit and he draws well once again. Can continue to improve with racing and looks the one to beat. AHREA (4) was only 1.9L off the winner at Northam last time out and will find this a little easier than what she raced in last time out. The inside barrier can see her sit a touch closer in the run back out to the  mile and she can put her best foot forward. BEST RESULT (2) ran over the top to score her maiden win here last time out. She maps for a similar run this time around and Galati replaces the apprentice hoop. Can repeat the dose. BLOW BACK (6) can build on the first-up effort. BE MY BELLE (5) is next best.
